## ğŸ“ System Architecture (UML)

The following Class Diagram illustrates how the `User` base class branches into specific roles, and how they interact with the `Book` inventory.

```mermaid
classDiagram
    %% Styling the diagram
    classDef base fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef sub fill:#bbf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef resource fill:#dfd,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;

    class User:::base {
        <<Abstract>>
        -String name
        -String id
        +login()
        +logout()
    }
    
    class Admin:::sub {
        +addBook()
        +removeBook()
        +viewReports()
    }
    
    class Student:::sub {
        -double fineAmount
        +borrowBook()
        +returnBook()
        +payFine()
    }

    class Book:::resource {
        -String isbn
        -String title
        -boolean isAvailable
        +getDetails()
        +setAvailability()
    }

    User <|-- Admin : Inherits
    User <|-- Student : Inherits
    Admin "1" --> "*" Book : Manages
    Student "1" --> "*" Book : Borrows
